## Notes and References

### Notes

*   ^ In 1947, Weill explicitly disavowed *[Life (magazine)](/Life_(magazine))*'s characterization of him as "a German composer," writing in a letter to the publication: "Although I was born in Germany I do not consider myself a 'German composer'.... I am an American citizen and during my dozen years in this country have composed exclusively for the American stage.... I would appreciate your straightening out your readers on this matter."

